CARAPACE. Six anterior setae; frontal process triangular (
Fig. 82D
). Small granules densely scattered between ocular triads and among sulci. Median eyes reduced to eyespots below tegument; median ocular tubercle absent (
Fig. 82A
); pair of setae in place of median ocular tubercle; lateral eyes extremely reduced, present only as small yellowish eyespots below tegument.

PEDIPALPS. Coxal dorsal carina with four prominent setae encircled by round carina and three setae on margin. Femur with three dorsal spines and three ventral spines (
Fig. 82E–F
); long spine between dorsal spines 1 and 2; two prominent setiferous tubercles between dorsal spine 1 and proximal margin; long spine between ventral spine 1 and proximal margin. Patella with four dorsal spines in primary series, proximal three spines long, fourth spine shorter (
Fig. 82E
); prominent setiferous tubercle distal to spine I, one-fourth length of spine I; three ventral spines (
Fig. 82F
); prominent spine between spine I and distal margin. Tibia with ventral spine distally and two setae between spine and distal margin. Tarsus with long dorsal spine, half length of tarsus (
Fig. 82C
); cleaning organ with 26 setae in ventral row.

